a|title=The Imaginary Institution of India: Politics and Ideas|year=2010|publisher=Columbia University Press|isbn=978-0231152235|ref= harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Kaur|first=Raminder|title=Performative Politics and the Cultures of Hinduism: Public Uses of Religion in Western India|date=5 February 2005|publisher=Anthem|isbn=978-1843311393|ref= harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Murphy|first=Eamon|title=Contemporary State Terrorism: Theory and Practice|date=24 March 2011|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0415664479|editor=Richard Jackson |editor2=Eamon Murphy |editor3=Scott Poynting|ref= harv}}\n* {{cite web|last=Markovits|first=Claude|title=India from 1900 to 1947|url=http://www.massviolence.org/India-from-1900-to-1947?cs=print#outil_sommaire_3|publisher=Mass Violence.Org|ref= {{sfnref|Markovits}} }}\n* {{cite book|last=Metcalf|first=Barbara|title=Schooling Islam: The Culture and Politics of Modern Muslim Education|year=2006|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=978-0691129334|editor=Robert W. Hefner |editor2=Muhammad Qasim Zaman|ref= harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Metcalf|first=Barbara|title=Communalism and Globalization in South Asia and its Diaspora|year=2013|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0415857857|editor=Deana Heath |editor2=Chandana Mathur|ref= harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Mazzarella|first=William|title=Censorium: Cinema and the Open Edge of Mass Publicity|year=2013|publisher=Duke University Press|isbn=978-0822353881|ref= harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Metcalf|first=Barbara D.|title=Islam in South Asia in Practice|year=2009|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=978-0691044200|editor=Barbara D. Metcalf|ref= harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Price|first=Daniel E.|title=Sacred Terror: How Faith Becomes Lethal|year=2012|publisher=Praeger|isbn=978-0313386381|ref= harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Prakash|first=Gyan|title=The Crisis of Secularism in India|date=15 February 2007|publisher=Duke University Press|isbn=978-0822338468|editor=Anuradha Dingwaney Needham |editor2=Rajeswari Sunder Rajan|ref= 